def multiplication_table(n):
    table = []
    for i in range(1, n + 1):
        row = []
        for j in range(1, n + 1):
            row.append(i * j)
        table.append(row)
    return table
The outer loop walks through each row number i from 1 to n, and the inner loop builds that row by multiplying i by every column number j, so the final table holds every i*j product.
